The soul, which is the life of the body, also is an organizing principle of that body. "Energy and Structure Are Interdependent at Every Level", metabolic energy generates structure. In Aristotelian tradition ensoulment occurs at conception because the soul is the "form-creator".

Fr. de Young keeps hammering this, but: if the soul is simply "the life of the body" (as opposed to a "thing"), then Dr. Ray Peat's thesis that "nerve cell metabolism *is* consciousness" from the 2021 "Thought and energy, mood and metabolism" newsletter is basically 100% correct.

The soul is necessarily present as the ovum turns into an organism. The soul is creating the process. If a cell is alive and has a metabolism, then it by definition also has a soul. It's very evident Aristotle's view of the soul, Christianity, and "metabolism" in biology overlap.
